import React from 'react';

const CricketBatIcon = () => {
  return (
    <svg
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
      width="48"
      height="48"
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      fill="none"
      className="cricket-bat-icon"
    >
      {/* Bat Blade */}
      <rect
        x="6"
        y="5"
        width="12"
        height="14"
        fill="#8d6e63"
        stroke="#6d4c41"
        strokeWidth="1"
        rx="2"
        transform="rotate(30 12 12)" // Rotate the blade
      />
      
      {/* Bat Handle */}
      <rect
        x="10"
        y="17"
        width="4"
        height="6"
        fill="#6d4c41"
        stroke="#5d4037"
        strokeWidth="1"
        rx="1"
        transform="rotate(30 12 12)" // Rotate the handle
      />
      
      {/* Top of the Bat */}
      <path
        d="M12 3l-3 2l3 1.5l3-1.5l-3-2z"
        fill="#4e342e"
        stroke="#3e2723"
        strokeWidth="1"
        transform="rotate(30 12 12)" // Rotate the top of the bat
      />
    </svg>
  );
};

export default CricketBatIcon;
